{
  "text": "In areas where vegetative cover is low (< 40%) and the soil surface is exposed, the reflectance of light in the red and near-infrared spectra can influence vegetation index values. This is especially problematic when comparing different soil types that may reflect different amounts of light in the red and near infrared wavelengths. SAVI was developed as a modification of the NDVI to correct the influence of soil brightness when vegetative cover is low [CITATION_1] . where:",
